Bhoomitra is a solar-powered, IoT-based compost and soil health monitoring system designed for Tier 2/3 cities. It automates compost moisture control using ESP32, sensors, and MQTT, and visualizes data using Grafana and Power BI.

## Features
- Moisture + temperature sensing
- IR belt + water pump control
- LCD + LED feedback
- Solar-powered + battery backup
- MQTT-based data sync

## Usage
1. Flash code to ESP32 using firmware/main.py
2. Connect sensors per `hardware/wiring_diagram.png`
3. Connect to MQTT broker and view dashboard

